title: Homoeosoma impressale
text:
Homoeosoma impressale is a species of <a href="Pyralidae">snout moth</a> in the genus "<a href="Homoeosoma">Homoeosoma</a>". It was described by <a href="George%20Duryea%20Hulst">George Duryea Hulst</a> in 1886. It is found in North America, including <a href="Arizona">Arizona</a> and <a href="California">California</a>.
The larvae feed on seeds and seed coats within the flower heads of various "<a href="Cirsium">Cirsium</a>" species (including "<a href="Cirsium%20canescens">Cirsium canescens</a>" and "<a href="Cirsium%20occidentale">Cirsium occidentale</a>") and closely related genera.
